  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How do I choose between Burgundy and Oregon Pinot Noir for dinner parties?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Oregon Pinot Noir offers more approachable fruit-forward flavors and typically provides better value for casual entertaining, making it ideal for guests unfamiliar with Burgundy's earthier profile. Burgundy excels with sophisticated menus featuring game, aged cheeses, or complex French preparations where its mineral complexity and terroir expression shine. Consider your menu's complexity and your guests' wine experience when deciding.</p>
